You can apply the [Object Mother][1] pattern here and create a global factory class to construct objects for multiple tests to reduce boilerplate code. In case your object structure changes, you&#39;ll only have to touch a single file (at best).

Tom Hombergs wrote a great article where he showcased the [Object Mother in combination with the builder pattern](https://reflectoring.io/objectmother-fluent-builder/).

In the end, you&#39;ll have something like the following:

```
CourseMother.completedCourse();
CourseMother.emptyCourse();
// etc.
```


  [1]: https://martinfowler.com/bliki/ObjectMother.html

